definition: name of various places including Gold Coast (Australian city), Gold Coast (former British colony in Africa) and Costa Daurada (area on the coast of Catalonia, Spain)
gold/chemical element Au/generic term for lustrous and ductile metals/money/golden/highly respected/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]
ocean/sea/CL:個|个[ge4],片[pian4]/great number of people or things/(dialect) numerous

sentences.english: Shanghai is the golden seacoast of East.
sentences.chinese: 上海是东方的黄金海岸。

sentences.english: What impresses me most in Brisbane is the Golden Coast.
sentences.chinese: 对布里斯班市印象最深的就是黄金海岸了。

sentences.english: Ghana was colonized as the Gold Coast by the British.
sentences.chinese: 迦纳曾被英国作为黄金海岸，是其殖民地。

sentences.english: I should have walked to gold coast .
sentences.chinese: 远远的地方有一堆建筑物，就是黄金海岸。

sentences.english: Brisbane or Gold Coast, they are really good for living.
sentences.chinese: 布村或者黄金海岸真的是很适合生活。

sentences.english: Who needs clichéd gold coast when wehave central coast!
sentences.chinese: 我们已经有中央海岸了，谁还要老旧的黄金海岸啊。

sentences.english: A commercial port, a golden seacoast, an investment capable of appreciation, the ideal choice.
sentences.chinese: 贸易港口，黄金海岸，投资增值，理想选择。

sentences.english: GoldCoast watch out, here we come.
sentences.chinese: 黄金海岸可要注意了，我们来了。
